{{Infobox noble | name = Shimotsuke no Iwashiro | image = | image_size = | caption = | period = Late [[Asuka period]] - Early [[Nara period]] | birth_date = Unknown | death_date = Unknown | other_names = | posthumous_name = | shinto_name = | Buddhist_name = | burial_place = | court_Rank = [[Junior Fifth Rank|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade]]; [[Kyōshiki|Governor of the Left Capital]] | ruler = [[Emperor Monmu]] → [[Empress Genmei]] → [[Empress Genshō]] | clan = {{ill|Shimotsukeno clan|ja|下毛野氏|1=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Shimotsukeno no Ason) → Shimotsukeno no Kawachi no Ason | parents = | siblings = | spouse = | children = | notes = }}
'''Shimotsuke no Iwashiro''' (下毛野 石代) was a Japanese noble active from the late [[Asuka period]] to the early [[Nara period]]. He held the Rank of [[Junior Fifth Rank|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade]] and served as [[Kyōshiki|Governor of the Left Capital]].
== Career == In the first year of the [[Taihō (Japan)|Taihō era]] (701), upon the death of the [[Sadaijin|Minister of the Left]] {{ill|Tajihi no Shima|ja|多治比嶋|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Iwashiro delivered a eulogy on behalf of the entire court while holding the Rank of [[Junior Seventh Rank|Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade]]. In the fourth year of [[Keiun]] (707), following a petition by his kinsman {{ill|Shimotsuke no Komaro|ja|下毛野古麻呂|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Iwashiro’s family name was changed from {{ill|Shimotsukeno clan|ja|下毛野氏|1=Shimotsukeno clan|lt=Shimotsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Shimotsukeno no Ason) to Shimotsukeno no Kawachi no Ason.
At the end of the [[Wadō era]] (715), Iwashiro was promoted from [[Junior Sixth Rank|Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade]] to [[Junior Fifth Rank|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade]] by an exceptional three-Rank promotion. During the reign of [[Empress Genshō]], he served as [[Kyōshiki|Governor of the Left Capital]]. In the fourth year of [[Yōrō]] (720), when a rebellion by the [[Emishi]] in [[Mutsu Province]] led to the death of the [[Mutsu Azechi|Inspector of Mutsu]], {{ill|Kamitsukeno no Hirohito|ja|上毛野広人|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Iwashiro was appointed Vice Commander of the expeditionary force under General {{ill|Tajihi no Agatamori|ja|多治比縣守|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Court Positions == According to the ''[[Shoku Nihongi]]'': * [[Taihō (Japan)|Taihō]] 1 (701), 7th month, 21st day: Held the Rank of [[Junior Seventh Rank|Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade]]. * [[Keiun]] 4 (707), 3rd month, 22nd day: Changed name from Shimotsukeno no Ason to Shimotsukeno no Kawachi no Ason. * Unknown date: Promoted to [[Junior Sixth Rank|Junior Sixth Rank, Upper Grade]]. * [[Wadō]] 8 (715), 1st month, 10th day: Promoted to [[Junior Fifth Rank|Junior Fifth Rank, Lower Grade]] (special three-Rank promotion). * Unknown date: Appointed [[Kyōshiki|Governor of the Left Capital]]. * [[Yōrō]] 4 (720), 9th month, 29th day: Appointed Vice Commander for the expedition against the Emishi.
== References == * [[Ujitani Misao]] (1992). ''Shoku Nihongi'' (Volume 1), [[Kōdansha]] Academic Library.
